1
00:00:17,768 --> 00:00:19,979
-What are you doing tonight?
-Nothing new.

2
00:00:20,062 --> 00:00:22,148
I'll go home and listen
to my wife complain

3
00:00:22,273 --> 00:00:26,235
that the boss pays a measly salary
and I work extra hours.

4
00:00:27,027 --> 00:00:28,571
Step on the gas.

5
00:00:28,738 --> 00:00:30,156
Let's get there before seven

6
00:00:30,239 --> 00:00:31,741
and watch the new Salman Khan film.

7
00:00:31,824 --> 00:00:34,660
If you buy me the ticket,
I'll get you there before seven.

8
00:00:34,744 --> 00:00:36,078
Done, buddy.

9
00:00:36,954 --> 00:00:38,998
What's going on?

10
00:00:39,498 --> 00:00:41,208
Looks like there was an accident.

11
00:00:42,376 --> 00:00:43,878
Get rid of this!

12
00:00:44,003 --> 00:00:45,379
Let's get the hell out of here!

13
00:00:48,215 --> 00:00:50,426
You there! Stop!

14
00:00:51,802 --> 00:00:56,056
-Stop! Damn you!
-Get out!

15
00:00:56,140 --> 00:00:58,100
Where are you coming from?

16
00:00:58,184 --> 00:00:59,351
From the market.

17
00:00:59,435 --> 00:01:00,978
I see.
What's your name?

18
00:01:02,062 --> 00:01:04,190
Cat got your tongue, fucker?

19
00:01:04,440 --> 00:01:07,067
Let's see some ID, shall we?

20
00:01:07,693 --> 00:01:09,195
Feroz Ahmed.

21
00:01:09,612 --> 00:01:11,113
-What are you carrying in the truck?
-Nothing.

22
00:01:11,197 --> 00:01:12,448
-Is it beef?
-No, it's not beef.

23
00:01:12,531 --> 00:01:14,283
Check the back of the truck.

24
00:01:15,785 --> 00:01:18,245
-What is it? Tell me.
-It's mutton.

25
00:01:18,496 --> 00:01:19,789
Mutton?

26
00:01:20,456 --> 00:01:21,791
-Bhaskar!
-Yes?

27
00:01:21,874 --> 00:01:23,626
These motherfuckers
are carrying beef!

28
00:01:24,460 --> 00:01:26,337
Motherfucker!

29
00:01:26,420 --> 00:01:28,380
Brother, it's not beef.
I swear to God!

30
00:01:28,464 --> 00:01:30,841
Fucker, come out!
How dare you!

31
00:01:31,509 --> 00:01:33,719
Come here, motherfucker!
I'll show you!

32
00:01:33,803 --> 00:01:35,304
Did you really think

33
00:01:35,387 --> 00:01:38,891
that if you'll kill our holy cow
we won't do anything about it?

34
00:01:38,974 --> 00:01:41,227
We'll slaughter all of you!

35
00:01:46,357 --> 00:01:48,108
You dare slaughter
the holy cow, our mother?

36
00:01:48,192 --> 00:01:49,652
You will be slaughtered too!

37
00:01:50,236 --> 00:01:52,196
Beat the fuck out of them!

38
00:01:52,363 --> 00:01:53,697
Hold him straight!

39
00:01:56,826 --> 00:01:58,202
Motherfucker!

40
00:02:17,221 --> 00:02:21,058
Two men, Amjad Ali, 
 and Feroz Ahmed

41
00:02:21,141 --> 00:02:24,687
were beaten to death 
 by a mob outside Pune

42
00:02:24,770 --> 00:02:26,272
under suspicion of carrying beef.

43
00:02:26,355 --> 00:02:30,693
One died on the spot and the other, 
 on the way to the hospital.

44
00:02:30,776 --> 00:02:33,362
Investigations reveal the meat 
 was not even beef--

45
00:02:33,487 --> 00:02:35,030
Why do you watch such news?

46
00:02:35,406 --> 00:02:37,283
Is it going to stop them
from doing such things?

47
00:02:37,575 --> 00:02:39,285
That's not what I meant.

48
00:02:39,577 --> 00:02:41,036
Then what do you mean, Jonali?

49
00:02:41,370 --> 00:02:43,038
You want me to stop
thinking about this?

50
00:02:43,581 --> 00:02:46,166
Kareem, you can retaliate.
But not through anger.

51
00:02:46,250 --> 00:02:48,544
Retaliate through your work,
the way you always do.

52
00:02:49,503 --> 00:02:51,297
Mere words won't help.

53
00:02:52,882 --> 00:02:56,427
Kareem, such thoughts don't make
you any different from them.

54
00:02:58,804 --> 00:03:01,056
This is the only language
they understand.

55
00:03:02,308 --> 00:03:05,060
Because people have
become numb from within.

56
00:03:05,936 --> 00:03:08,898
They watch such news every day
and then they say...

57
00:03:09,690 --> 00:03:11,358
"What's going on in this country?"

58
00:03:11,692 --> 00:03:13,152
And that's it!

59
00:03:13,986 --> 00:03:16,030
People have a five-minute
attention span these days.

60
00:03:16,697 --> 00:03:17,781
After five minutes

61
00:03:17,865 --> 00:03:19,825
they watch a funny video,
and forget everything.

62
00:03:19,909 --> 00:03:21,035
Kareem, please!

63
00:03:22,119 --> 00:03:24,079
Stop being this negative!

64
00:03:24,622 --> 00:03:27,416
Sometimes, you seem
scarier than them.

65
00:03:28,375 --> 00:03:30,586
That's good.
Today, you're scared

66
00:03:30,920 --> 00:03:33,005
-tomorrow, they'll be.
-Oh, shut up, Kareem!

67
00:03:33,088 --> 00:03:35,049
Not everyone's wielding a sword.

68
00:03:35,424 --> 00:03:37,426
But the ones with the swords
are calling the shots.

69
00:03:54,068 --> 00:03:54,944
Hello.

70
00:03:57,529 --> 00:03:58,906
Are you new here?

71
00:03:59,156 --> 00:04:01,116
-Yes.
-Got cigarettes?

72
00:04:02,076 --> 00:04:03,243
No.

73
00:04:03,410 --> 00:04:04,495
Give me a cup of tea.

74
00:04:05,037 --> 00:04:07,665
I'll need to make it.
It'll take time.

75
00:04:13,921 --> 00:04:14,838
No!

76
00:04:15,255 --> 00:04:16,423
Don't touch the teddy bear.

77
00:04:16,632 --> 00:04:18,217
-Will you make the tea or not?
-You really want it?

78
00:04:18,300 --> 00:04:20,177
I thought you won't wait for just a cup.

79
00:04:20,302 --> 00:04:23,097
-It will take time.
-Do you not want customers?

80
00:04:23,555 --> 00:04:24,974
You come here to sleep?

81
00:04:33,399 --> 00:04:35,943
-Hello, this is Shinde.
 -What's the update?

82
00:04:36,235 --> 00:04:38,654
I've been watching the box
since I arrived.

83
00:04:38,737 --> 00:04:40,656
I'll let you know if something happens.

84
00:04:56,171 --> 00:04:58,173
Bulletproof glass!

85
00:04:59,174 --> 00:05:00,634
You know why it's here?

86
00:05:00,926 --> 00:05:03,345
So that your fellow terrorists
can't attack you.

87
00:05:03,679 --> 00:05:05,222
Then, there's us fools...

88
00:05:06,056 --> 00:05:08,350
trying to save your life.

89
00:05:08,934 --> 00:05:11,478
Tell me the truth.
What's Zulfiqar?

90
00:05:13,605 --> 00:05:15,024
Zulfiqar?

91
00:05:17,026 --> 00:05:18,485
Mission Zulfiqar.

92
00:05:19,153 --> 00:05:21,780
I don't know anything
about this mission.

93
00:05:22,990 --> 00:05:25,492
-I just want to see my mother--
-If you loved your mother so much

94
00:05:25,576 --> 00:05:27,411
why the hell did you go to Syria?

95
00:05:34,460 --> 00:05:36,795
Do you remember the 2002 riots?

96
00:05:40,716 --> 00:05:42,384
At that time...

97
00:05:43,969 --> 00:05:45,971
my uncle used to live in Baroda.

98
00:05:47,347 --> 00:05:50,684
Mom, Dad and my sister were visiting him.

99
00:05:51,101 --> 00:05:53,395
They didn't step out of the house
for two days.

100
00:05:56,440 --> 00:05:57,816
They were hoping...

101
00:05:58,442 --> 00:06:01,570
that the riots would end soon.

102
00:06:02,946 --> 00:06:04,782
But they didn't.

103
00:06:07,701 --> 00:06:09,161
Two days later...

104
00:06:09,745 --> 00:06:11,413
a mob entered the house.

105
00:06:15,459 --> 00:06:18,128
My mother and sister hid under the bed.

106
00:06:21,882 --> 00:06:23,842
They witnessed it all.

107
00:06:27,513 --> 00:06:30,599
They watched the mob slaughter
my father and my uncle.

108
00:06:36,730 --> 00:06:38,732
My sister screamed involuntarily.

109
00:06:41,527 --> 00:06:44,571
Those bastards dragged them out...

110
00:06:48,283 --> 00:06:50,327
and thrashed them like animals!

111
00:06:59,044 --> 00:07:02,339
My mom wasn't lucky enough.
She survived.

112
00:07:05,134 --> 00:07:06,593
Since then...

113
00:07:06,969 --> 00:07:09,096
she wakes up screaming
every single night.

114
00:07:11,140 --> 00:07:13,767
My father, sister, and my uncle...

115
00:07:15,477 --> 00:07:17,604
appear in her dreams every night.

116
00:07:22,359 --> 00:07:23,986
You have a family as well.

117
00:07:24,069 --> 00:07:25,904
If something like this
would've happened to them...

118
00:07:26,822 --> 00:07:28,240
what would you do?

119
00:07:30,576 --> 00:07:34,371
I can't even imagine what
your family went through.

120
00:07:36,123 --> 00:07:39,793
But an eye for an eye...

121
00:07:42,546 --> 00:07:44,548
will leave the whole world blind.

122
00:07:48,218 --> 00:07:50,345
You want to meet your mother, right?

123
00:07:50,554 --> 00:07:53,015
Then tell me something useful.

124
00:07:53,640 --> 00:07:56,643
You're not going to stay here
as a patient forever.

125
00:07:57,603 --> 00:07:59,813
Think, Moosa!

126
00:08:08,655 --> 00:08:09,740
Excuse me.

127
00:08:09,823 --> 00:08:11,700
Smoking is not allowed in the hospital.

128
00:08:15,579 --> 00:08:18,498
-Where is it allowed, then?
-Outside the hospital.

129
00:08:24,463 --> 00:08:26,798
Moosa, I'll be back.

130
00:08:35,766 --> 00:08:38,268
The students of Victoria College
have always been this way.

131
00:08:38,518 --> 00:08:40,270
They just call themselves "students."

132
00:08:40,354 --> 00:08:42,481
But in fact, they're always
bitching about the country.

133
00:08:43,982 --> 00:08:46,193
And I'm sure you're right.

134
00:08:46,693 --> 00:08:48,362
I suspect them too.

135
00:08:48,737 --> 00:08:51,198
One of those bastards
is responsible for the blast.

136
00:08:51,281 --> 00:08:52,950
Do you suspect anybody in particular?

137
00:08:53,367 --> 00:08:54,993
Someone with a criminal record
or something.

138
00:08:55,077 --> 00:08:58,121
I have the list ready.
They're all anti-nationals.

139
00:08:59,081 --> 00:09:01,083
Alright. Okay...

140
00:09:01,166 --> 00:09:03,585
Tell me the names of the ones
with prior arrest warrants.

141
00:09:04,169 --> 00:09:05,420
There are four.

142
00:09:05,545 --> 00:09:07,339
The first one is Junaid.

143
00:09:07,631 --> 00:09:09,466
He's been studying here for two years.

144
00:09:09,591 --> 00:09:11,635
Then, there's Sait,
who's been here for three years.

145
00:09:11,718 --> 00:09:13,428
Sajid. He took up
a three-year course

146
00:09:13,512 --> 00:09:15,847
but has been at it
for six years now!

147
00:09:16,014 --> 00:09:17,557
Amir Peeran, he's from Pune.

148
00:09:17,641 --> 00:09:19,851
But he used to study 
 in Saudi Arabia before.

149
00:09:34,157 --> 00:09:35,617
All of them are in custody, sir.

150
00:09:35,701 --> 00:09:36,743
Hold on!

151
00:09:36,827 --> 00:09:38,704
I asked you to make a list.

152
00:09:38,912 --> 00:09:41,123
How could you arrest them
without a warrant?

153
00:09:41,206 --> 00:09:43,583
Don't worry about the warrant, sir.

154
00:09:43,750 --> 00:09:46,545
Leave it to me.
It's a routine.

155
00:09:46,628 --> 00:09:48,338
And these bastards are elusive.

156
00:09:48,588 --> 00:09:50,173
Let's use our time with them wisely.

157
00:09:50,257 --> 00:09:53,218
-They are locked up in a cell here. 
-Okay, I'm on my way.

158
00:09:54,970 --> 00:09:56,847
Why have you arrested us?

159
00:09:57,014 --> 00:09:58,181
Do you have a warrant?

160
00:09:58,265 --> 00:10:01,310
Bloody motherfucker!
This is my warrant!

161
00:10:01,435 --> 00:10:03,145
Want me to shove it up?

162
00:10:04,146 --> 00:10:05,272
Fucker!

163
00:10:06,356 --> 00:10:09,192
You've arrested us
because we are Muslims.

164
00:10:09,318 --> 00:10:11,778
Damn it! Has he lost it?

165
00:10:11,862 --> 00:10:12,946
Sir...

166
00:10:13,447 --> 00:10:15,866
Sir, I don't even know them.

167
00:10:15,949 --> 00:10:18,243
-Why am I here with--
-Shut up!

168
00:10:18,368 --> 00:10:21,872
-You're a fucking coward.
-Don't call me a coward.

169
00:10:22,497 --> 00:10:24,875
-I am nothing like you.
-Shut the hell up!

170
00:10:25,042 --> 00:10:27,836
You think you're here to gossip?

171
00:10:28,003 --> 00:10:30,422
Just answer my questions, that's it!

172
00:10:30,547 --> 00:10:33,216
Sir, we don't know anything
about the bomb blast.

173
00:10:33,300 --> 00:10:35,052
Why are you questioning us?

174
00:10:35,135 --> 00:10:37,137
You piece of shit!

175
00:10:49,983 --> 00:10:51,443
Hello, sir.

176
00:10:52,319 --> 00:10:55,947
Do you have any evidence
on the ones you have arrested?

177
00:10:56,031 --> 00:10:57,449
What will we do with evidence, sir?

178
00:10:57,532 --> 00:10:58,867
-We already know everything.
-Really?

179
00:10:58,950 --> 00:11:00,702
They're all anti-nationals.

180
00:11:00,786 --> 00:11:02,788
Sir, they were partying
on the day of the blast.

181
00:11:03,747 --> 00:11:06,875
And if Pakistan wins
a match against India

182
00:11:06,958 --> 00:11:08,585
they'll party all night!

183
00:11:08,668 --> 00:11:10,504
And that makes them anti-national?

184
00:11:11,254 --> 00:11:13,298
Have you lost it, Jadhav?

185
00:11:13,382 --> 00:11:15,634
Sir, you'd asked me to
conduct an investigation

186
00:11:15,759 --> 00:11:18,136
and to round up
suspects in the college, right?

187
00:11:18,220 --> 00:11:19,846
Sir, just give me two days.

188
00:11:19,971 --> 00:11:22,099
I'll shove a baton up their asses
and get the truth out.

189
00:11:22,307 --> 00:11:24,226
You'll get a written confession.

190
00:11:26,353 --> 00:11:28,438
Do you want a written confession

191
00:11:28,605 --> 00:11:30,357
with a baton shoved
up their asses?

192
00:11:32,943 --> 00:11:35,278
What a waste of time!

193
00:11:35,487 --> 00:11:36,863
Any movement at the drop box?

194
00:11:36,988 --> 00:11:38,824
Crows are shitting on it.
Nothing else.

195
00:11:39,199 --> 00:11:41,576
The local police have the place
under 24/7 surveillance.

196
00:11:41,660 --> 00:11:43,703
I hope they don't doze off.

197
00:11:43,787 --> 00:11:45,372
I hope so, too.

198
00:11:56,925 --> 00:11:58,802
For fuck's sake!

199
00:11:58,927 --> 00:12:00,053
Get lost!

200
00:12:01,972 --> 00:12:03,849
Don't touch the teddy bear, asshole!

201
00:12:04,850 --> 00:12:05,934
Get lost!

202
00:12:28,248 --> 00:12:29,666
-Yeah, Arvind?
-Hi, Suchi.

203
00:12:29,749 --> 00:12:32,002
-Where are you?
 -What happened?

204
00:12:32,878 --> 00:12:35,338
-Are you going home?
-Yeah, why?

205
00:12:35,422 --> 00:12:37,591
I'm at Potluck.

206
00:12:37,716 --> 00:12:39,384
Can you come over for fifteen minutes?

207
00:12:39,468 --> 00:12:41,887
I want to discuss something important.
It's a bit urgent.

208
00:12:42,596 --> 00:12:44,556
Yes, I can.
But what happened?

209
00:12:44,639 --> 00:12:46,892
Just come over. 
 It won't take long.

210
00:12:46,975 --> 00:12:49,644
Call me when you reach Potluck.

211
00:12:49,895 --> 00:12:50,896
Okay.

212
00:12:53,398 --> 00:12:55,150
Please stop here.

213
00:13:04,117 --> 00:13:06,161
Welcome, ma'am.
Do you have a reservation?

214
00:13:06,244 --> 00:13:08,246
-Yeah--
-Hey, Suchi!

215
00:13:09,498 --> 00:13:10,832
Thanks for coming.

216
00:13:11,082 --> 00:13:13,793
I want to introduce you to
the CEO of my company, Nikhil.

217
00:13:13,877 --> 00:13:15,003
What?

218
00:13:15,712 --> 00:13:17,631
-I mean... How?
-It's okay.

219
00:13:17,714 --> 00:13:19,674
It's just a casual meeting,
nothing formal.

220
00:13:19,758 --> 00:13:21,468
Once you meet him,
it'll be easier for you.

221
00:13:21,551 --> 00:13:22,677
What will be easier?

222
00:13:22,761 --> 00:13:25,305
To decide whether you want to join us.

223
00:13:26,097 --> 00:13:27,390
What are you talking about?

224
00:13:27,891 --> 00:13:30,644
Arvind, first of all,
I don't know what you do.

225
00:13:30,727 --> 00:13:33,605
I have no idea what
I will do in this company.

226
00:13:34,064 --> 00:13:35,524
And what will I say?

227
00:13:35,607 --> 00:13:37,609
You're great with people,
so just relax.

228
00:13:37,692 --> 00:13:39,778
And it's a start-up.
We're not a corporate structure.

229
00:13:39,861 --> 00:13:42,489
Knowing you, you'll easily learn
on the job, in no time.

230
00:13:42,572 --> 00:13:44,115
I think you'll be great.

231
00:13:44,199 --> 00:13:45,116
Trust me!

232
00:13:45,200 --> 00:13:47,536
I wish I had as much confidence
in myself as you do!

233
00:13:47,619 --> 00:13:49,955
You know what the secret
to confidence is?

234
00:13:50,163 --> 00:13:51,665
Pretend to be confident.

235
00:13:52,082 --> 00:13:54,292
-Nikhil, this is Suchitra.
-Hi!

236
00:13:54,376 --> 00:13:55,835
So, you are Suchi.

237
00:13:56,086 --> 00:13:57,837
-Nice meeting you, finally.
-Nice meeting you too.

238
00:13:57,921 --> 00:13:59,464
It's okay if I call you Suchi, right?

239
00:13:59,548 --> 00:14:01,341
-Yeah, of course.
-Please sit.

240
00:14:02,676 --> 00:14:04,636
Arvind's always talking about you.

241
00:14:05,637 --> 00:14:07,639
I'm glad Arvind convinced you.

242
00:14:07,806 --> 00:14:09,307
I promise, you won't regret it.

243
00:14:10,517 --> 00:14:12,185
So what made you change
your mind?

244
00:14:12,269 --> 00:14:14,729
I mean, do you have an idea
what exactly we do

245
00:14:14,938 --> 00:14:17,065
what our goals are,
what our plans are?

246
00:14:20,569 --> 00:14:21,778
Well...

