555
00:31:18,502 --> 00:31:19,670
What do you mean?

556
00:31:19,753 --> 00:31:21,422
You haven't visited us for so long.

557
00:31:21,505 --> 00:31:22,923
Do you even remember the
last time visited us?

558
00:31:23,007 --> 00:31:24,216
There's too much work at the office.

559
00:31:24,300 --> 00:31:25,843
I just don't have time.

560
00:31:29,263 --> 00:31:30,889
Yeah, he often says that his mother--

561
00:31:30,973 --> 00:31:31,807
Shut up! Will you?

562
00:31:31,890 --> 00:31:33,183
I mean, he always talks about her.

563
00:31:33,267 --> 00:31:35,352
-He thinks about you all the time.
-Whatever!

564
00:31:35,436 --> 00:31:36,729
Once we settle the home loan

565
00:31:36,812 --> 00:31:38,814
we'll move somewhere else
so Mom can stay with us.

566
00:31:38,897 --> 00:31:40,566
No chance.

567
00:31:40,816 --> 00:31:43,152
-Mom has settled in Powai.
-Shut up!

568
00:31:43,235 --> 00:31:45,404
She's got a few good friends there.

569
00:31:59,335 --> 00:32:02,588
-Dad.
-Yes, darling. Tell me.

570
00:32:03,839 --> 00:32:07,468
Hello, Laxmi.
How are you?

571
00:32:07,551 --> 00:32:09,261
Hello!

572
00:32:09,553 --> 00:32:11,764
Thanks to the grace of Swami,
we're all well!

573
00:32:11,847 --> 00:32:13,599
How are you and your wife?

574
00:32:13,682 --> 00:32:16,310
Thanks to Lord Ayyappan's grace,
we're all good!

575
00:32:16,393 --> 00:32:18,812
Two melodious cultures
come together

576
00:32:19,063 --> 00:32:20,898
to create a huge din!

577
00:32:21,148 --> 00:32:22,524
Dad, here.

578
00:32:22,608 --> 00:32:26,570
Why is he talking so loudly?
Does he think we're deaf?

579
00:32:26,654 --> 00:32:28,906
Is she deaf?
Why is she screaming so much?

580
00:32:28,989 --> 00:32:30,699
Come on, Dad!

581
00:32:31,075 --> 00:32:32,034
Where's Mom?

582
00:32:32,117 --> 00:32:35,746
She had some urgent work
at the Matunga Tamil Association.

583
00:32:35,829 --> 00:32:38,582
-What are they chattering about in Tamil?
-Mom!

584
00:32:39,208 --> 00:32:41,085
I hope they aren't talking about us!

585
00:32:41,168 --> 00:32:42,169
Please don't start.

586
00:32:42,419 --> 00:32:43,921
-Hello, Grandpa!
-Come here.

587
00:32:44,004 --> 00:32:45,339
How are you, darling?

588
00:32:46,382 --> 00:32:47,549
Where's your elder sister?

589
00:32:47,633 --> 00:32:49,343
Thank you, Grandpa.
Same to you!

590
00:32:50,552 --> 00:32:51,470
What is this?

591
00:32:51,553 --> 00:32:52,888
Doesn't he understand Tamil?

592
00:32:52,971 --> 00:32:56,517
Why don't you talk in Hindi?
Let us in on the conversation.

593
00:32:56,600 --> 00:32:58,769
Today, India is going to be split apart!

594
00:32:58,852 --> 00:33:00,312
All I am saying is...

595
00:33:00,604 --> 00:33:03,065
children should learn
their mother tongue.

596
00:33:03,148 --> 00:33:07,152
It's enough to know the
national language, Hindi.

597
00:33:07,444 --> 00:33:09,822
Hindi is not our
national language, ma'am.

598
00:33:09,905 --> 00:33:11,407
-Please!
-What?

599
00:33:11,490 --> 00:33:13,409
Hindi is just one of the
official languages, ma'am.

600
00:33:13,492 --> 00:33:15,536
Don't you realize the
importance of Hindi?

601
00:33:15,619 --> 00:33:18,372
Hindi has evolved from Sanskrit.

602
00:33:18,455 --> 00:33:21,250
And Sanskrit is the
world's oldest language.

603
00:33:21,333 --> 00:33:23,836
But Tamil is much
older than Sanskrit.

604
00:33:23,919 --> 00:33:25,254
Says who?

605
00:33:25,504 --> 00:33:27,881
It is a fact.

606
00:33:48,110 --> 00:33:49,945
Seriously? What are we watching?
Switch it off!

607
00:33:50,028 --> 00:33:52,740
We've been told to keep
a constant watch on them.

608
00:33:53,198 --> 00:33:55,367
-We can't miss anything.
-Milind!

609
00:33:55,492 --> 00:33:56,535
Punit!

610
00:33:58,996 --> 00:34:01,206
You never let me do my job.

611
00:34:07,671 --> 00:34:09,715
Lower the volume.

612
00:34:11,467 --> 00:34:15,012
Happy birthday to you!

613
00:34:15,429 --> 00:34:18,766
Happy birthday to you!

614
00:34:18,891 --> 00:34:23,103
Happy birthday, dear Atharv!

615
00:34:23,270 --> 00:34:26,774
Happy birthday to you!

616
00:34:27,399 --> 00:34:29,902
-Smear some cake on his face.
-No!

617
00:34:30,944 --> 00:34:32,279
It's the first piano I've ever eaten.

618
00:34:32,362 --> 00:34:34,448
-Okay, Atharv!
-Dad!

619
00:34:36,575 --> 00:34:37,910
Feed the camera!

620
00:34:41,121 --> 00:34:42,247
-It's good.
-Thank you.

621
00:34:42,331 --> 00:34:43,332
You bought it from Madras?

622
00:34:43,415 --> 00:34:45,083
No, from Matunga.

623
00:34:45,167 --> 00:34:47,503
Not everything is from Madras.

624
00:34:48,545 --> 00:34:51,173
I hope it doesn't have egg in it.

625
00:34:53,091 --> 00:34:55,552
Will I ever offer you
a cake with egg in it?

626
00:34:56,678 --> 00:34:58,931
I called up the
bakery just for you

627
00:34:59,014 --> 00:35:00,516
and gave him
strict instructions

628
00:35:00,599 --> 00:35:02,810
to give me an eggless cake!

629
00:35:03,227 --> 00:35:05,270
Come on, eat up.

630
00:35:11,109 --> 00:35:12,444
Did you ever think

631
00:35:12,820 --> 00:35:14,530
you would have to do something like this?

632
00:35:14,988 --> 00:35:16,490
Watch people make out?

633
00:35:18,075 --> 00:35:19,284
I know.

634
00:35:19,618 --> 00:35:21,036
But we just need to do certain things.

635
00:35:21,119 --> 00:35:23,622
A lot of it feels wrong.

636
00:35:24,706 --> 00:35:26,166
But I keep reminding myself

637
00:35:26,250 --> 00:35:27,876
I am doing this for the greater good.

638
00:35:28,293 --> 00:35:29,503
Hopefully.

639
00:35:35,259 --> 00:35:37,135
Guys, come in, we have a guest.

640
00:35:37,219 --> 00:35:38,220
Let's go.

641
00:35:38,679 --> 00:35:40,430
-Did you get the van?
-Yes.

642
00:35:41,473 --> 00:35:43,350
-When are we getting the stuff?
-Tomorrow.

643
00:35:43,851 --> 00:35:44,852
Who is it?

644
00:35:45,185 --> 00:35:46,186
I'm not sure.

645
00:35:46,270 --> 00:35:48,522
-Did Nissar get the floor plan? 
 -Yes.

646
00:35:50,482 --> 00:35:52,359
-Guest list? 
 -He's on it.

647
00:35:52,442 --> 00:35:54,111
He said he'll get it
directly to the base camp.

648
00:35:54,194 --> 00:35:55,696
He didn't want to email it.

649
00:35:55,779 --> 00:35:57,531
-I had asked him not to.
-You're right.

650
00:35:57,614 --> 00:35:59,324
You never know who's sniffing around.

651
00:35:59,408 --> 00:36:00,492
Fuck!

652
00:36:01,201 --> 00:36:02,703
They're planning something big.

653
00:36:03,537 --> 00:36:04,872
Good.

654
00:36:06,498 --> 00:36:08,333
This biryani is good.

655
00:36:08,500 --> 00:36:10,294
But, if you'd put some meat in it

656
00:36:10,377 --> 00:36:12,045
it would've been more delicious!

657
00:36:12,129 --> 00:36:13,338
Keep your voice down!

658
00:36:14,423 --> 00:36:16,884
If my father-in-law hears that,
you'll be slaughtered.

659
00:36:16,967 --> 00:36:19,303
Please! Your mom is the same!

660
00:36:20,304 --> 00:36:22,389
People are getting
slaughtered in the name of biryani.

661
00:36:22,472 --> 00:36:24,474
And we think the ISIS is brutal!

662
00:36:26,310 --> 00:36:27,477
-Suchi!
-Yes?

663
00:36:27,561 --> 00:36:29,688
Please tell him to take up an IT job.

664
00:36:29,771 --> 00:36:32,608
He's not going to listen to anyone.
Let him be!

665
00:36:32,691 --> 00:36:33,817
Why don't you leave this job?

666
00:36:33,901 --> 00:36:36,486
You've been serving the
country long enough.

667
00:36:36,862 --> 00:36:38,739
Now it's time to work for yourself.

668
00:36:39,239 --> 00:36:41,033
JK, please convince him.

669
00:36:41,116 --> 00:36:43,201
Okay, but who'll convince me?

670
00:36:43,744 --> 00:36:45,037
Stop it, Suren.

671
00:36:45,120 --> 00:36:46,872
Don't start the same old conversation!

672
00:36:46,955 --> 00:36:48,165
Listen, Suchi.

673
00:36:48,332 --> 00:36:51,960
When Srikant was in school
he was everyone's darling.

674
00:36:52,502 --> 00:36:56,214
Everyone thought he
would make it big!

675
00:36:56,715 --> 00:36:58,967
That he'd be successful.
And what did he do?

676
00:36:59,134 --> 00:37:03,555
He became a patriot and
got a government job.

677
00:37:03,639 --> 00:37:04,765
Stop it!

678
00:37:05,682 --> 00:37:07,601
Everyone has their own priorities.

679
00:37:07,935 --> 00:37:10,270
He wants to serve the nation.
It's his choice!

680
00:37:10,354 --> 00:37:12,898
Listen, all I am saying is

681
00:37:12,981 --> 00:37:15,901
his job should pay him good, right?

682
00:37:16,443 --> 00:37:18,236
Just being patriotic
is not enough

683
00:37:18,320 --> 00:37:19,905
to fill up your bank account.

684
00:37:20,864 --> 00:37:23,033
In fact, even I am serving the nation.

685
00:37:23,116 --> 00:37:25,494
-I'm boosting the economy!
-Really?

686
00:37:25,619 --> 00:37:27,371
Do you think you can
boost the economy

687
00:37:27,454 --> 00:37:28,872
if the country is not safe?

688
00:37:28,956 --> 00:37:31,124
-Let's shut down everything.
-Sri!

689
00:37:31,208 --> 00:37:32,918
Try boosting the economy then!

690
00:37:33,627 --> 00:37:35,420
We're fucking morons, aren't we?

691
00:37:35,921 --> 00:37:38,173
Change the topic!

692
00:37:38,256 --> 00:37:40,634
Let's boost the party, not the economy.

693
00:37:40,717 --> 00:37:43,011
-Good point!
-Sri, one couplet.

694
00:37:43,095 --> 00:37:45,472
-I'm not in the mood!
-Come on!

695
00:37:45,555 --> 00:37:47,557
-Please!
-One couplet, please!

696
00:37:48,642 --> 00:37:51,061
What's that word? Irshad!

697
00:37:51,353 --> 00:37:52,729
Let me think.

698
00:37:54,314 --> 00:37:55,941
Okay, here goes.

699
00:37:56,274 --> 00:37:59,152
"There is no hope now...

700
00:38:02,114 --> 00:38:04,241
There is no hope now

701
00:38:04,491 --> 00:38:07,285
I can't find that lovely face now

702
00:38:07,411 --> 00:38:10,330
Once I used to laugh at my heart

703
00:38:10,622 --> 00:38:12,874
Nothing makes me laugh now"

704
00:38:15,502 --> 00:38:16,628
What does it mean?

705
00:38:16,712 --> 00:38:18,213
Now, one has to first say a couplet

706
00:38:18,296 --> 00:38:21,091
and then explain it to this generation.

707
00:38:21,466 --> 00:38:23,677
Because there was no hashtag
in the couplet.

708
00:38:23,760 --> 00:38:26,680
There's one for people like you too.
Listen!

709
00:38:26,888 --> 00:38:28,390
This is an original one.

710
00:38:28,515 --> 00:38:31,935
"There was a time when you could see
God in children..."

711
00:38:32,686 --> 00:38:36,398
When we were children,
one could see God within us.

712
00:38:37,065 --> 00:38:40,485
"There was a time when you could see
God in children..."

713
00:38:41,069 --> 00:38:44,156
But now you see children
Only on Instagram"

714
00:38:44,239 --> 00:38:46,491
You should be on Instagram, okay?

715
00:38:46,575 --> 00:38:48,785
Wasting your 1000 grams of brain
on Instagram!

716
00:38:49,953 --> 00:38:52,330
-One more.
-Okay, let me think.

717
00:38:52,748 --> 00:38:54,708
-Cover your ears.
-Why?

718
00:38:54,791 --> 00:38:57,002
Can you ever listen to your father?

719
00:38:57,961 --> 00:38:59,629
Come on, Dhriti.

720
00:38:59,796 --> 00:39:01,298
Cover your ears, please!

721
00:39:01,465 --> 00:39:04,009
"Her youth would incite
A jaljala inside me"

722
00:39:04,134 --> 00:39:05,927
"Jaljala" means volcano.

723
00:39:07,804 --> 00:39:08,680
Correct!

724
00:39:08,764 --> 00:39:12,142
"Her youth would incite
A jaljala inside me

725
00:39:12,642 --> 00:39:15,520
I know it would make my heart burst

726
00:39:16,188 --> 00:39:17,481
But my phone always rang first"

727
00:39:19,691 --> 00:39:21,902
-Ditto.
-Did you hear that?

728
00:39:28,658 --> 00:39:30,202
I need to go.

729
00:39:30,744 --> 00:39:33,371
-It's kind of urgent.
-Just two more couplets.

730
00:39:33,455 --> 00:39:35,123
-It's an emergency.
-Do you need to go?

731
00:39:35,248 --> 00:39:36,958
Suchi, it is an emergency.

732
00:39:37,584 --> 00:39:39,878
Sorry! You guys, continue.

733
00:40:08,782 --> 00:40:10,075
Talpade...

734
00:40:13,870 --> 00:40:16,164
I read Suchi's messages.

735
00:40:17,124 --> 00:40:18,959
You've started checking Suchi's phone?

736
00:40:19,042 --> 00:40:20,585
No, I wasn't checking.

737
00:40:21,253 --> 00:40:24,339
I went into the room,
her phone was on the shelf.

738
00:40:24,923 --> 00:40:27,425
And she got a text, so...

739
00:40:28,176 --> 00:40:30,679
What's that thing called...
"Review"?

740
00:40:30,804 --> 00:40:33,265
-Preview
-Yes, the preview, on the screen.

741
00:40:33,473 --> 00:40:36,017
I read that.
I wasn't checking her phone.

742
00:40:36,101 --> 00:40:37,269
Of course, you weren't.

743
00:40:37,352 --> 00:40:38,520
You were just reading her messages.

744
00:40:38,603 --> 00:40:41,022
Fucker!
Will you listen to what I'm saying?

745
00:40:41,940 --> 00:40:43,567
Stop preaching!

746
00:40:48,029 --> 00:40:51,700
-Her colleague--
-Tiwari, have you lost your mind?

747
00:40:52,742 --> 00:40:54,619
Don't jump to conclusions!

748
00:40:54,703 --> 00:40:58,039
Who texts a lady in the
middle of the night?

749
00:41:00,125 --> 00:41:02,294
-And, Suchi--
-What?

750
00:41:05,046 --> 00:41:07,215
I've been noticing her.

751
00:41:09,926 --> 00:41:12,179
She's always on the phone,
like a teenager.

752
00:41:12,596 --> 00:41:13,680
So what?

753
00:41:14,347 --> 00:41:16,099
If you won't talk to her

754
00:41:16,183 --> 00:41:18,059
she'll need someone else to talk, right?

755
00:41:18,143 --> 00:41:20,604
Fucker! I'll throw you out of the car!

756
00:41:20,729 --> 00:41:23,106
-What kind of a friend are you?
-Tell me something.

757
00:41:23,440 --> 00:41:25,901
-Did you read her replies?
-No!

758
00:41:29,863 --> 00:41:33,491
But that jackass is
sending her dozens of emo...

759
00:41:33,575 --> 00:41:34,576
-Emojis.
-Right, emojis!

760
00:41:34,659 --> 00:41:36,119
-Smileys.
-Yes, smileys.

761
00:41:37,120 --> 00:41:38,538
What do you mean by "dozens"?

762
00:41:42,000 --> 00:41:43,710
I mean...

763
00:41:46,296 --> 00:41:47,881
Lots of emojis at once!

764
00:41:47,964 --> 00:41:50,217
Is there a fixed number
of smileys to be sent?

765
00:41:50,300 --> 00:41:52,385
Will you land in trouble if you send more?

766
00:41:52,469 --> 00:41:54,221
All of this is very normal.

767
00:41:54,304 --> 00:41:55,555
We also do it, don't we?

768
00:41:56,765 --> 00:41:58,475
And Suchi is not a child.

769
00:41:59,309 --> 00:42:02,312
She can handle this kind of attention.

770
00:42:04,105 --> 00:42:05,774
She'll take care of it.

771
00:42:08,068 --> 00:42:09,903
The smiley that you mentioned...

772
00:42:10,153 --> 00:42:12,072
Was it a normal one or like...

773
00:42:13,698 --> 00:42:18,536
The one with a red heart on the lips.

774
00:42:18,828 --> 00:42:19,829
Was it that one?

775
00:42:20,664 --> 00:42:22,415
No, not that one.

776
00:42:23,458 --> 00:42:24,542
Then you're safe.

777
00:42:24,626 --> 00:42:26,127
-I'm safe?
-Yeah.

778
00:42:33,593 --> 00:42:35,345
Milind, what's happening?

779
00:42:35,428 --> 00:42:37,597
Sir, a guy named Iqbal came to meet him.

780
00:42:37,722 --> 00:42:39,474
They were talking
about some delivery

781
00:42:39,557 --> 00:42:40,809
which will happen tomorrow.

782
00:42:40,892 --> 00:42:42,060
And, sir...

783
00:42:42,143 --> 00:42:44,604
they were also talking about
a guest list and a floor plan.

784
00:42:44,688 --> 00:42:47,524
Some guy called Nissar
is coordinating this.

785
00:42:47,607 --> 00:42:49,901
We haven't seen him until now
but he can come any time.

786
00:42:49,985 --> 00:42:52,570
Get me Iqbal's and Nissar's details.

787
00:42:52,904 --> 00:42:54,072
Find out who they are.

788
00:42:54,155 --> 00:42:55,532
Already done, sir.

789
00:43:01,121 --> 00:43:02,831
What? What happened?

790
00:43:02,914 --> 00:43:04,124
Must be a power cut, sir.

791
00:43:04,207 --> 00:43:05,917
Oh, shit!

792
00:43:07,836 --> 00:43:08,795
Milind.

793
00:43:08,878 --> 00:43:11,131
Go stand outside the hostel gate
and stay there.

794
00:43:11,298 --> 00:43:13,008
Keep an eye on things.

795
00:43:36,781 --> 00:43:38,742
Milind, what's the status?

796
00:43:38,825 --> 00:43:40,618
I'm at the hostel's front gate.

797
00:43:40,702 --> 00:43:42,662
There's a power cut.
No activity here.

798
00:43:42,746 --> 00:43:44,581
-Stay alert!
 -Sir.

799
00:44:06,770 --> 00:44:07,937
Fuck!

800
00:44:12,025 --> 00:44:12,859
-Sir!
-Yes?

801
00:44:12,942 --> 00:44:15,028
Sir, a van just passed 
 by from the side lane.

802
00:44:15,111 --> 00:44:16,154
What kind of van?

803
00:44:16,237 --> 00:44:19,491
I ran behind it but 
 I couldn't see the number.

804
00:44:19,741 --> 00:44:21,242
I'm damn sure Kareem was in it!

805
00:44:21,326 --> 00:44:23,661
-Kareem?
 -Yes, sir.

806
00:44:27,916 --> 00:44:28,792
Sorry, sir.

807
00:44:31,211 --> 00:44:33,671
Why did you think we were being watched?

808
00:44:34,130 --> 00:44:36,508
A couple of days ago,
a tea stall suddenly popped up

809
00:44:36,591 --> 00:44:38,343
and then disappeared.

810
00:44:38,676 --> 00:44:40,762
Did you see the van
outside gate number five?

811
00:44:40,845 --> 00:44:42,430
It's been there all this time.

812
00:44:42,514 --> 00:44:44,224
There are cigarette butts
strewn all around it.

813
00:44:44,307 --> 00:44:45,892
I might be overthinking it but...

814
00:44:46,184 --> 00:44:47,602
I can't afford to take a risk.
